rograms that are local regional serving the six state geographic area of IL IN MI MN OH WI and national if supportEmptyParas endif Objective 1 The NASA Glenn Research Center shall develop a LAP for LEP persons if supportEmptyParas endif Target Date June 30 2001 if supportEmptyParas endif Responsible Officials Center Director EO Officer Chief Information Officer CIO Director of External Programs Chief of Educational Programs Office and Chief of Community and Media Relations Office if supportEmptyParas endif Element 1 Assessment Needs and Capacity NASA Glenn Research Center GRC shall have in place mechanisms to assess on an ongoing basis the LEP status and language assistance needs of their target audience s in their respective conducted programs and activities as well as mechanisms to assess their capacity to meet those needs according to the elements of this plan if supportEmptyParas endif 1 1 1 Define a reporting system examples a quarterly request for input a form to be completed for each request received etc that will provide assistance in defining a metric for assessing success Be sure to include cost information in such a system Based on the information received make modifications as needed in the LAP if supportEmptyParas endif Responsibility EO Officer for overall assessment various employees particularly Media and Community Relations Education Office Webmaster and CIO to ensure reporting occurs if supportEmptyParas endif Due Date Define the reporting system by the end of FY01 measure against metrics each year if supportEmptyParas endif 1 1 2 Present the LAP to the Director and Senior Staff and after their approval utilize various media Newsletter Today Glenn EO Web site Aerospace Frontier etc to notify GRC employees of the purpose and mechanics of the LAP Make sure that those who have responsibility are clearly defined and notified so they will understand their accountability if supportEmptyParas endif Responsibility Center Director and EO Officer if supportEmptyParas endif Due Date Present the LAP and begin the process of notifying GRC employees by the end of FY01 provide informational updates annually based on the metrics if supportEmptyParas endif 1 1 3 Advertise the LAP to our customers outside of GRC especially in communities with LEP persons Have a statement on our Home Page and utilize handouts news releases and other outlets so our customers know of the LEP Advertisements for specific events should also have a statement concerning the availability of assistance for LEP persons if applicable if supportEmptyParas endif Responsibility EO Officer working with other responsible components if supportEmptyParas endif Due Date Begin advertising as soon as GRC employees have been notified estimated to be first half of FY02 Assess modify if necessary and provide reminders to the public annually if supportEmptyParas endif Element 2 Oral Language Assistance NASA Glenn Research Center will arrange for the provision of oral language assistance to LEP persons in both face to face and telephone encounters in its conducted programs and activities where such assistance is requested and or anticipated if supportEmptyParas endif 1 2 1 Proactively identify resources that can be used based on anticipated requests from the public for oral language assistance GSA maintains a source sheet the local community may also be a good source depending on the program and the requested need For example we know we ll want to start offering Visitor Center tours for LEP persons identify bilingual GRC employees ahead of time and ask for their assistance based on their response we may need to procure a formal interpreter The same applies for requests for Speakers booth staffers for certain Outreach events etc Responsibility EO Officer to begin the process and inform others Once informed it will be the responsibility of the individual offices to locate utilize and report on the resources that have been identified if supportEmptyParas endif Due Date Start the process by the end of FY01 Update as necessary each year if supportEmptyParas endif 1 2 2 Institute a formal process for identifying and asking for assistance from bilingual GRC employees Make sure the list is made available to support Center needs if supportEmptyParas endif Responsibility EO Officer to begin the process and inform others Once informed find a home for the responsibility in either External Programs or Human Resources as they deal with outreach education and GRC employee management respectively if supportEmptyParas endif Due Date Start the process by the end of FY01 Update as necessary each year if supportEmptyParas endif Element 3 Translation of Written Materials NASA Glenn Research Center will produce vital documents in languages other than English where there is a significant number or percentage of LEP persons in the target audience s of the respective conducted programs and activities These written materials may include but not be limited to paper and electronic documents such as program and or activity announcements notices web sites and correspondence if supportEmptyParas endif 1 3 1 Define the LEP target audiences for the local regional and national conducted programs and activities Utilize past history input from members of Speakers Bureau and other GRC employees as well as input from the local community if supportEmptyParas endif Responsibility EO Officer to oversee process of contacting internal and external sources to identify potential LEP target audiences Data should then be analyzed and shared with other responsible offices if supportEmptyParas endif Due Date Start the process by the end of FY01 Update as necessary each year if supportEmptyParas endif 1 3 2 Identify written materials to be translated Consider level of material appropriateness for translation and impact in furthering NASA s mission In most cases entry level materials will be considered appropriate Visitor Center brochures Education Program brochures Human Resources brochures etc however education materials and handouts for class use may also be appropriate Informational web sites should also be identified Responsibility EO Officer to meet with the appropriate people to identify materials for translation EO Officer to also identify potential funding sources for translation and printing costs Metrics should also be established to ensure that materials translated are used if supportEmptyParas endif Due Date Start the process by the end of FY01 Measure use as needed and redefine needs annually if supportEmptyParas endif 1 3 3 Identify LEP sources for announcements notices and news releases Define when it would be appropriate to have multilingual media prepared and ensure that responsible employees understand that criteria if supportEmptyParas endif Responsibility EO Officer to meet with Media Relations and any other responsible personnel to outline the requirements needed document the process and disseminate to DLT and GRC employees Media Relations to define LEP sources internally document their process and explain to their employees if supportEmptyParas endif Due Date Start the process by the end of FY01 Measure use as needed and redefine needs annually if supportEmptyParas endif Element 4 Procedures NASA Glenn Research Center shall have in place specific procedures related to each of the plan elements and designated staff who will be responsible for implementing activities relating to their respective LAP if supportEmptyParas endif 1 4 1 Define and document procedures to be used in the administration of the LAP Be sure that each element has procedures and that responsible staff are identified and held accountable for their activities As a minimum these procedures should be reviewed annually if supportEmptyParas endif Responsibility EO Officer to maintain written procedures and provide annual review and any updates as necessary if supportEmptyParas endif Due Date Start the process by the end of FY01 Written procedures should be in place by the end of FY02 Review and updates should be completed annually if supportEmptyParas endif Element 5 Notification of Availability of Free Language Services NASA Glenn Research Center shall inform the target audiences of its conducted programs and activities through oral or written notice in the relevant primary language that free language assistance is available if supportEmptyParas endif 1 5 1 Based on LEP target audiences already defined begin the task of notifying these audiences that free language assistance is available Notices can be added to already existing written materials web pages can be modified to include a statement and outreach personnel can include such a statement in their presentations if supportEmptyParas endif Responsibility EO Officer to coordinate this process in the beginning with transition to responsible offices once the process is set up if supportEmptyParas endif Due Date Start the process once the internal components are ready Estimate this to be no later than mid FY02 if supportEmptyParas endif Element 6 Staff Training NASA Glenn Research Center will provide training to appropriate program staff on the policies and procedures of its respective language assistance activities if supportEmptyParas endif 1 6 1 Provide high level briefings to members of Senior Staff provide in depth briefings to those with responsibilities tied to LAP s provide overview briefings to interested GRC employees and utilize newsletters Today Glenn web sites and Aerospace Frontiers to disseminate basic information concerning GRC s LAP to the GRC population if supportEmptyParas endif Responsibility EO Officer to provide these briefings and coordinate with any other personnel needed as part of the briefing process EO Officer to work with responsible persons to utilize various media needed to disseminate basic information to the GRC population if supportEmptyParas endif Due Date Begin the process by the end of FY01 Continue into FY02 until are defined briefings information dissemination has taken place Provide briefings updates on an as needed basis annually if supportEmptyParas endif Element 7 Monitoring Accessibility and Quality NASA Glenn Research Center will institute procedures to monitor the accessibility and quality of language assistance activities for LEP persons in its conducted programs and activities if supportEmptyParas endif 1 7 1 Ensure that those with LAP responsibilities understand the need for recordkeeping and feedback and that they understand that changes will be made to the LAP as needed This initial LAP represents a beginning with future LAP s to evolve based on monitoring feedback and changes as necessary They need to understand that they have a critical role in this process Measurements need to be taken regularly and those in the loop need to hear the feedback so they can understand the continuous nature of the changes as they are implemented Responsibility EO Officer to ensure that information is shared as the metrics of the LAP are measured and changes are made if supportEmptyParas endif Due Date Begin the process with the briefings explained in 1 6 1 Continue to provide updates as needed if supportEmptyParas endif 1 7 2 Identify the personnel with primary responsibility for analyzing and updating the LAP as needed This person should have access to needed information and the ability to gather information as needed at least on an annual basis if supportEmptyParas endif Responsibility EO Officer to designate the LAP report writer if supportEmptyParas endif Due Date Designation should be made in conjunction with the briefings explained in 1 6 1 if supportEmptyParas endif if supportEmptyParas endif Objective 2 In the interim the NASA Glenn Research Center in the conduct of its respective programs or activities shall respond to requests for language assistance in a manner that ensures equal access by LEP persons to NASA programs and activities if supportEmptyParas endif Target Date Immediately 